    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-12-09T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-12-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">792.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/12–953:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 407<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Thailand (<persName type="from"
                            >Parsons</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-12-09T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 9, 1953—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1168. Reference <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1139.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d407fn1">
                        <ref target="#d405">Document 405</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Part III of lV—<gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss>.</p>
                <p>This message includes summary recommendations for <gloss target="#t_USIS1"
                        >USIS</gloss> carried Ambassador Donovan.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USIS1">USIS</gloss> program coverage requirements include
                    adjacent areas as approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d407fn2">Reference is presumably to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss>-approved portion of <ref target="#d403">Document
                        403</ref>.</note> New Thai political-psychological efforts require <gloss
                        target="#t_USIS1">USIS</gloss> support (see reference telegram). Need
                    continue publicize accomplishments United States emphasize Communist threats and
                    emphasize joint efforts United States with peoples <gloss target="#t_SEA1"
                        >SEA</gloss> preserve freedom and cultural integrity.</p>
                <p>Accomplishment program depends designation competent personnel and provision
                    adequate funds. Need $1.25 million recommended recent <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> action<note n="3" xml:id="d407fn3">This figure was recommended
                        in the Financial Appendix to <gloss target="#t_PSB1">PSB</gloss> D–23, not
                        printed. The National Security Council did not approve the Appendix,
                        however, but deferred decision on the question of seeking additional funds;
                        see <ref target="#d400">Document 400</ref>.</note> as minimum. Also need
                    increase personnel.</p>
                <p>Specifics recommended program include (1) propaganda offensive against
                    infiltration from Thai autonomous state, (2) informing Thai of threat to
                    monarchy, religion, tradition of independence, (3) develop method of dealing
                    with Vietnamese refugees Thailand, (4) aid Associated States exposing Viet Minh
                    threat <gloss target="#t_SEA1">SEA</gloss> using cultural ties Laos, Cambodia
                    and Thai, (5) expand Chinese program in Thailand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Parsons</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
